//■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■
// Gets requests from the football-data.org API using the final String API_KEY and a request URL line
// to finish the BASE_URL final String.
//
public class FootballAPIv2 {
    private static final String API_KEY = "a1656790c3c4408593f44ac696c80b47";      // API authorization key
    private static final String BASE_URL = "https://api.football-data.org/v2/";    // URL used for API Data Access
    private static final int REFRESH_MINUTES = 10;                                 // Minutes between refreshes of game data

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Create a scheduled executor service to fetch data every 10 minutes
        ScheduledExecutorService executorService = Executors.newScheduledThreadPool(1);

        // Schedule the data gathering task
        executorService.scheduleAtFixedRate(() -> {
            try {
                // Make an API request to fetch game data
                String gameData = fetchDataFromAPI("matches");

                // Process the game data (e.g., extract wins and losses)
                processGameData(gameData);

            } catch (Exception e) {
                e.printStackTrace();
            }
        }, 0, REFRESH_MINUTES, TimeUnit.MINUTES); // Fetch data every 10 minutes

        // Shutdown hook to gracefully shut down the executor service
        Runtime.getRuntime().addShutdownHook(new Thread(() -> {
            // Print shutdown message to console
            System.out.println("Shutting down the application...");

            // Shutdown the executor service
            executorService.shutdown();
            try {
                // Wait 5 seconds for processes to finish and termination to occur
                if (!executorService.awaitTermination(5, TimeUnit.SECONDS)) {
                    // Forcefully terminate if not terminated in 5 seconds
                    executorService.shutdownNow();
                }
            } catch (InterruptedException e) {
                // Forcefully terminate if interrupted
                executorService.shutdownNow();
            }
        }));

        // Keep the application running until manually terminated
        while (true) {
            try {
                // Sleep for 1 second or perform other tasks
                Thread.sleep(1000);
            } catch (InterruptedException e) {
                e.printStackTrace();
            }
        }
    }

    private static String fetchDataFromAPI(String endpoint) throws Exception {
        // Create a URL for the API endpoint
        URL url = new URL(BASE_URL + endpoint);

        // Open a connection to the URL
        HttpURLConnection connection = (HttpURLConnection) url.openConnection();
        connection.setRequestMethod("GET");
        connection.setRequestProperty("X-Auth-Token", API_KEY);

        // Read the API response
        int responseCode = connection.getResponseCode();
        if (responseCode == HttpURLConnection.HTTP_OK) {
            BufferedReader in = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(connection.getInputStream()));
            StringBuilder response = new StringBuilder();
            String inputLine;
            while ((inputLine = in.readLine()) != null) {
                response.append(inputLine);
            }
            in.close();
            return response.toString();
        } else {
            throw new Exception("Failed to fetch data from the API. Response code: " + responseCode);
        }
    }

    private static void processGameData(String gameData) {
        try {
            // Parse the JSON string into a JSONObject
            JSONObject jsonData = new JSONObject(gameData);

            // Extract the count and filters data
            int count = jsonData.getInt("count");
            JSONObject filters = jsonData.getJSONObject("filters");
            String dateTo = filters.getString("dateTo");
            String permission = filters.getString("permission");
            String dateFrom = filters.getString("dateFrom");

            System.out.println("Count: " + count);
            System.out.println("Filters:");
            System.out.println("  permission: " + permission);
            System.out.println("  dateFrom: " + dateFrom);
            System.out.println("  dateTo: " + dateTo);

            // Extract and iterate through the matches array
            JSONArray matches = jsonData.getJSONArray("matches");
            System.out.println("Matches:\n");
            for (int i = 0; i < matches.length(); i++) {
                JSONObject match = matches.getJSONObject(i);
                int matchday = match.getInt("matchday");
                JSONObject score = match.getJSONObject("score");
                String homeTeamName = match.getJSONObject("homeTeam").getString("name");
                String awayTeamName = match.getJSONObject("awayTeam").getString("name");

                // Handle null values in score data
                int homeScore = 0;
                int awayScore = 0;
                if (!score.isNull("fullTime")) {
                    JSONObject fullTimeScore = score.getJSONObject("fullTime");
                    homeScore = fullTimeScore.optInt("homeTeam", 0);
                    awayScore = fullTimeScore.optInt("awayTeam", 0);
                }

                String competitionName = match.getJSONObject("competition").getString("name");
                String utcDate = match.getString("utcDate");
                String status = match.getString("status");

                System.out.println("  Matchday: " + matchday);
                System.out.println("  Home Team: " + homeTeamName);
                System.out.println("  Away Team: " + awayTeamName);
                System.out.println("  Home Score: " + homeScore);
                System.out.println("  Away Score: " + awayScore);
                System.out.println("  Competition: " + competitionName);
                System.out.println("  UTC Date: " + utcDate);
                System.out.println("  Status: " + status);

                // Extract and print the score data
                String duration = score.getString("duration");
                String winner = score.optString("winner", "N/A");

                System.out.println("  Score Data:");
                System.out.println("    Duration: " + duration);
                System.out.println("    Winner: " + winner);

                JSONObject penalties = score.getJSONObject("penalties");
                int awayTeamPenalties = penalties.optInt("awayTeam", 0);
                int homeTeamPenalties = penalties.optInt("homeTeam", 0);

                System.out.println("    Penalties - Away Team: " + awayTeamPenalties);
                System.out.println("    Penalties - Home Team: " + homeTeamPenalties);

                System.out.println();
            }
        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}